1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
What if I told you nerves communicate through a traveling spike of electricity?

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:11,600
This electric spike, known as the action potential, is essential for sending signals in your body.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:18,000
Imagine billions of these spikes racing down neurons, orchestrating everything from a twitch to a thought.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:24,400
When a neuron fires, it opens ion channels, allowing sodium to rush in, creating that spike.

5
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,600
Then, potassium flows out to reset the neuron.

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:37,200
This rapid ion exchange travels down the neuron at lightning speed, relaying vital information throughout your body — all without you even knowing it.

7
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,200
